<p><strong>Every Student Should Have a Safe  Learning Environment</strong></p>
<p>  How  many students in your school or community have been harmed by bullying?<br />
  Be a  leader by showing that you care. You can take action with this guide designed  for students and educators to plan bullying prevention events in their school  or community.<br />
  This  five-step guide provides helpful information to create a meaningful event;  including how to form your committee, setting the date and location, planning  your activities, promoting your event, and holding the event.</p>
<p><img src="/images/pdficon_small.gif" width="15" height="15" alt="" /> <a href="/bullying/resources/toolkits/pdf/Pacer-Unite-Against-Bullying-School-Event-Planning-Guide.pdf" target="_blank">Download  the Unite Against Bullying - School Event Planning Guide</a><br />
</p>
